enhanced_by.reason: The wrap method performs the inverse operation of unwrap by wrapping elements with HTML, making it useful for setting up tests that require both operations.
Both methods modify the state of the elements by removing or altering their content, making empty useful for setting up tests that involve state changes.
The html method retrieves the inner HTML of elements, which can be used to verify the state of elements after unwrap has been applied.
The text method retrieves the combined text of all matched elements, which can be used to verify the text content after unwrap has been applied.
